			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just spent 10 Neh`Ashiir spawns to get torch, so I have this down pat (also a few Jade Reavers to pad the ole pocketbook). Here is my way, very much the same....
<br />

<br />
<img src="http://myweb.cableone.net/nweaver/nehcamp.jpg" border="0" />
<br />

<br />

<br />
(Optional step...get Neck gate reagents, bind outside of CoM for fast login farming)
<br />

<br />
1. Inivis up, and go to point "A" on the map. 
<br />
2. Watch for wanderers from the north and south Gazebo. Drop invis, summon up fluffy. Kit him up with Fists (Maybe kedge blades, not sure how ice lands on BR's) girdle and mask. BO5, DS. 
<br />
3. Clear south gazeebo, clear north Gazeebo. Clear the spawns on either side of the locked door (red dot to the left of "A"). 
<br />
4.Poke head through door, cast Eye of Zomm (Optional, hug your clay bracelet) target Black Reaver, back up to leading edge of the moat, facing directly at the door. 
<br />
5. /pet sit (prevents him from running when blinded)
<br />
6. Cast Mala to pull mob (Mala debuffs some FR, will land, and helps land your nukes)
<br />
7. BR will "Pop" outside right on you...back up while fluffy gets aggro. Remember step 4? if you get blinded, you can count to about 4 (on slow mount) and back up, wait for blind to wear off.
<br />
8. Heal pet some, and nuke (Fire based only) reaver. If you have focused pet, I prefer to nuke, as pet regens health so fast.
<br />
9. Reaver dies, another one spawns. You should be far enough away that you can med up/let pet regen as needed. 
<br />
10. /pet attack, rinse and repeat until Lord G Spawns
<br />
11. Lord G- Get him down to 50% as fast as you can without getting summoned, then heal pet up to 60% or so, and then he is a gimp. 
<br />
12. move to the north corridor (where point C is), killing along the way. (I just let pet tank them all, no nuking, just sitting on horse medding.) There is 6-7 spawns between A and B, with Gazeebo cleared. 
<br />
13. At point B, med to full mana (you wern't nuking that greenie yard trash, were you?)
<br />
14. type /pet kill a black reaver
<br />
15. assist pet, /pet back off
<br />
16. Cast Scars, hit BR for 500ish damage
<br />
17. Run to point "C" on the map. The reaver will not appear until you get close to point C, so be carefull. I like to pull the BR back to around point D for the killing, so that you avoid healing mobs in the castle area, and  have plenty of time on respawns (Gazeebo is about to respawn when you pull or has just respawned). 
<br />
18. /pet sit, again to prevent blinding problems
<br />
19. Neh has a tendancy to debuff, so just be ready. I think she is like Lord G, where she gets easier after 50% health. 
<br />
20. Loot up, and pray the gods of loot shine down  on you. 
<br />

<br />
My spell lineup was:
<br />
Sun Vortex
<br />
Scars of Sigil
<br />
DS
<br />
Mala
<br />
WoX
<br />
Gate
<br />
BOV (or 60 heal, in case Neh gets a lucky round in)
<br />
Planer Renewal
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Just for history sake......
<br />

<br />
1. Woodsman staff
<br />
2. Woodsman Staff
<br />
3. Woodsman Staff
<br />
4. Woodsman Staff
<br />
5. No Drop shield
<br />
6  No Drop Shield
<br />
7 Woodsman Staff
<br />
8 Woodsman Staff
<br />
9. Woodsman Staff
<br />
10 TORCH
<br />

<br />
If you have any questions, email me (nweaver@keylabs.com) or post here.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=542302" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://myweb.cableone.net/nweaver/gryyf.jpg" border="0" /></a>
<br />
Check out the stuff Fluffly let me loot!!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
