<br />

<br />
Gryyfindergirl's post is right on the money.  I have done it that way many times.  It works.  
<br />

<br />
I have two suggestions.  
<br />

<br />
1. Be aware of when the mobs in area D respawn.  When it is close to their spawn time, stop fighting the black reaver until you clear the spawns again.  It is very difficult for a mage to handle the add.  Especially if the pet is blinded and runs away instead of to the add.  Once Neh'Ashiir spawns, I strongly suggest you wait until you clear those spawns again until you attack him.  Nothing ruins your day like getting Neh'Ashiir to 20% and getting an add from a respawn and not being able to finish him off.  
<br />

<br />
2.  Have a summon pet available.  If the pet is blinded when it kills the black reaver, it will run off on its fear path.  If you summon it, it will be next to you and not run off.  It will then be available to help you incase of a respawn.  If you don't summon it, it will run along it's fear path until the blind wears off.  Then it may get stuck and not get back to you.  Best to summon it as soon as the black reaver dies.<br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=449337" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=449337</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
